is_common_ui_mode(25.10)                              is_common_ui_mode(25.10)

Name
       is_common_ui_mode - Checks if the Stylus Common UI mode is enabled

Syntax
       is_common_ui_mode

       [-help]

       Checks if the Stylus Common UI mode is enabled. This command is helpful
       if  you  are using both Common UI and Legacy UI, and you want to source
       their  respective  script  based  on  the  value  returned  by  is_com-
       mon_ui_mode.  In  such  scripts, if is_common_ui_mode returns 1, Stylus
       Common UI commands will be sourced, and if it returns 0, Legacy UI com-
       mands will be sourced.

       For example, you can write a script, which can be sourced  irrespective
       of UI, as below.

        if {[is_common_ui_mode]}

       {

        <Common UI commands>

        }

       else

       {

        <Legacy UI commands>

        }

Parameters
       None

       Example

       The following example checks it on the Innovus prompt:

       @innovus> is_common_ui_mode

       1

       innovus> is_common_ui_mode

       0

       Return value 1 indicates that the Stylus Common UI mode is enabled.

